Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech at the Associated Builders and Contractors (ABC) 2017 Legislative Conference in Washington, D.C. Pence expressed his appreciation for the organization and its members, highlighting their contributions to the economy and job creation. He emphasized President Trump's commitment to rebuilding America's infrastructure and creating jobs, as well as his efforts to repeal and replace Obamacare and implement tax reform. Pence also discussed the need for workforce development and vocational education to address the shortage of skilled workers in the construction industry. He encouraged ABC members to advocate for the President's agenda and work with their elected representatives to achieve these goals.